  "prompt": "What percentage of Quora users ask and answer questions?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Quora does not publicly release exact statistics on the percentage of users who ask and answer questions. However, it's known that a significant portion of Quora's user base is comprised of passive users who primarily consume content rather than actively participating by asking or answering questions.\n\nFrom various reports and analyses, it's often cited that on platforms like Quora, only about 10% to 20% of users are active contributors (those who ask and answer questions), while the majority are lurkers who read content without contributing. These figures can fluctuate based on several factors, including the platform's user base growth and changes in user engagement strategies.\n\nFor the most current and specific statistics, it would be necessary to consult Quora's own data or recent third-party research focused on user behavior on the platform.",
